                        <h4>Unequivocally open</h4>   
                    </div>
                    <hr id="hrgreen">
                    <P>
                        Citizenbuild is a vehicle for citizens and communities to come together, directly decide for themselves what they want to produce, and carry it out on a local basis in which everyone, unequivocally, can join in. We carry this out as a tech company that lets the community define what we will produce (globally crowdsourcing all R&D) and produce it themselves locally, employing themselves through our shareholding entities (user-owned temp agencies taking the form of local co-ops in every community). These co-ops provide all labour and manufacturing infrastructure required to carry out a Citizenbuild project locally.
                    </p>    
                    <p>    
                        Citizenbuild's terms of participation assure that users can place themselves into absolutely any project and absolutely any job of their choosing, whether we are talking about the production of basics like food and household items, or the largest engineering challenges the community might choose to set its sights on. 
                    </p>    
                    <p>    
                        Whatever the user’s location, they will be able to collaborate on precisely the same terms and conditions, meant to guarantee each user the right to work and produce locally what users have designed together. This is what allows Citizenbuild (from the standpoint of game theory) to break the economic stalemate or "prisoner’s dilemma” that has needlessly held back collaboration, innovation and productivity.
                    </p>    
                    <p>    
                        Since the co-ops own Citizenbuild, it is the first user-governed and user-owned tech company.
